<hl>
<seg id=1> Shantou hi-tech development zone favored by investors domestic and overseas </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Shantou, Dec 20th (Xinhua News Agency) With improving environment for investment and agreeable prospect for development, the Shantou High-tech Development Zone, in South China's Guangdong Province, has captured the attention of investors home and abroad. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Scientists of Chaozhou (a city in Guangdong) origin from the Silicon Valley of the US have expressed their willingness to establish high-tech industries in the hi-tech zone. The Director-general of Motorola in China and personnel concerning from Ericsson came to consult and bid for investment projects here. Manufacturers from Taiwan also prepare to set up software companies in the zone. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> At present, RMB 1.8 billion has been invested in the hi-tech zone, with a plant area of 370,000 square meters being built. Infrastructures such as water and electricity supply and communication facilities as well as bonded warehouses have come into use. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> By November this year, there have been 177 enterprises entered the zone, with an investment of RMB 6.4 billion, and half of the total is from overseas. Seven of them gained the status of the nation-level high-tech enterprise. </seg>
<seg id=6> The total industrial output value of the hi-tech zone this year aggregated to RMB 3.7 billion. The total revenue of technology, industries and trade exceeded RMB 4.55 billion. The export volume reached RMB 127,470,000. The hi-tech zone handed over RMB 0.36 billion of tax this year. </seg>
<seg id=7> Meanwhile, the city government has constituted over ten packages of regulations, measures and policies to encourage technology-and-knowledge intensive high-tech enterprises. </seg>
</p>
